HEADWORD: Dosser
<hw>Dos"ser</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>dosserum</ets>, or F.<ets>dossier</ets> bundle of papers, part of a
basket resting on the back, fr. L. <ets>dorsum</ets> back. See
<er>Dorsal</er>, and cf. <er>Dosel</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>dorser</asp> and <asp>dorsel</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
pannier, or basket.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To hire a ripper's mare, and buy new <qex>dossers</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hanging tapestry; a dorsal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dossier</ent>⟦br⟧
